  <span id="freeText12203922129700574238" style="display:none"><b>4 Stars</b><br /><br />I have been craving a medieval-set romance for awhile and was happy to find this book in a used bookstore especially since I know how much Quinn loves it. For me, Johanna is the star and the main reason why I could see myself re-reading it. I just loved seeing her develop into a confident young woman who ultimately ends up saving the day herself. Gabriel was appropriately alpha for the setting, but I liked the fact that he wasn't a jerk. His devotion to his clan and Johanna was nice to read about. I also thought it was interesting that I grew to like Gabriel as Johanna did. I thought the clan issues were intriguing and provided a nice background to the romance. As expected from Julie Garwood, the writing is beautiful and, while the pace is slow, it works well for the characters and the situation. </span>
